## 11. Spreadsheet Structure Example

| id      | top   | middle | footer | title                    | mobile                                      | desktop                                     |
|---------|-------|--------|--------|--------------------------|---------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| 123     | TRUE  | FALSE  | TRUE   | Special Pune Offer       | /assets/images/ads/pune-mobile.jpg          | /assets/images/ads/pune-desktop.jpg         |
| 456     | TRUE  | TRUE   | FALSE  | Mumbai Depot Discount    | /assets/images/ads/mumbai-mobile.jpg        | /assets/images/ads/mumbai-desktop.jpg       |
| global  | TRUE  | TRUE   | TRUE   | Plan Your Trip with MSRTC | /assets/images/ads/global-mobile.jpg        | /assets/images/ads/global-desktop.jpg       |
| my-blog | FALSE | TRUE   | FALSE  | Read Our Travel Blog     | /assets/images/ads/blog-mobile.jpg          | /assets/images/ads/blog-desktop.jpg         |

- `TRUE` / `FALSE` can be typed as boolean values in Google Sheets (checkbox) or as text. The JavaScript will treat `"TRUE"`, `true`, `"true"` as true; everything else as false.
- If an ad slot is `FALSE`, the corresponding container is hidden.
- If an ID is not found, **all three containers are hidden**.
- The `global` row is used for pages without a specific ID (home, bus-schedule, about, etc.).

